# Pages & routing (`src/pages/**`)

- **Default shell:** Most marketing pages use `BaseLayout` from `@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro` with optional `hideBigLogo`, `hideNavigation`, `hideFooter`.
- **Dynamic routes:** `[...slug].astro` maps `params.slug` to `entry.id` for `team`, `store`, `gallery`, `legal`, and `posts` (blog). Blog tag pages use `blog/tags/[tag].astro` with `params.tag`.
- **URL contracts (must stay consistent with cards/RSS):**
  - Blog posts: `/blog/posts/{id}` — see `src/components/blog/BlogCard1.astro`, `src/pages/rss.xml.js`
  - Tags: `/blog/tags/{tag}`
  - Team: `/team/{id}`
  - Store: `/store/{id}`
  - Gallery: `/gallery/posts/{id}` — see `GalleryCard1.astro`
  - Legal: `/legal/{id}`
- **Layouts per area:** `BlogLayout`, `TeamLayout`, `StoreLayout`, `GalleryLayout`, `LegalLayout` receive rendered Markdown via `<Content />` and pass `frontmatter` / `page.data` / `entry.data` as implemented in each `[...slug]` file.
- **No MDX:** Do not add `.mdx` unless the project adds `@astrojs/mdx` to `package.json` and `astro.config.mjs`.
